## Library: creativeprojects/go-selfupdate

Use `github.com/creativeprojects/go-selfupdate` (actively maintained; works with GoReleaser asset naming out of the box).

### Core Implementation

```go
package cmd

import (
    "context"
    "fmt"
    "runtime"

    selfupdate "github.com/creativeprojects/go-selfupdate"
    "github.com/spf13/cobra"
)

var upgradeCmd = &cobra.Command{
    Use:   "upgrade",
    Short: "Upgrade agentmap to the latest version",
    RunE:  runUpgrade,
}

func runUpgrade(cmd *cobra.Command, args []string) error {
    if version == "dev" {
        return fmt.Errorf("cannot upgrade a dev build; install a release version first")
    }

    checkOnly, _ := cmd.Flags().GetBool("check")

    updater, err := selfupdate.NewUpdater(selfupdate.Config{
        Validator: &selfupdate.ChecksumValidator{UniqueFilename: "checksums.txt"},
    })
    if err != nil {
        return fmt.Errorf("creating updater: %w", err)
    }

    latest, found, err := updater.DetectLatest(
        context.Background(),
        selfupdate.NewRepositorySlug("ryankelln", "agentmap"),
    )
    if err != nil {
        return fmt.Errorf("checking for updates: %w", err)
    }
    if !found {
        return fmt.Errorf("no releases found")
    }

    if latest.LessOrEqual(version) {
        fmt.Printf("Already up to date (%s)\n", version)
        return nil
    }

    if checkOnly {
        fmt.Printf("Update available: %s -> %s\n", version, latest.Version())
        return nil
    }

    exe, err := selfupdate.ExecutablePath()
    if err != nil {
        return fmt.Errorf("locating executable: %w", err)
    }

    if err := updater.UpdateTo(context.Background(), latest, exe); err != nil {
        // Check for permission error
        if os.IsPermission(err) {
            return fmt.Errorf("permission denied; try: sudo agentmap upgrade")
        }
        return fmt.Errorf("updating: %w", err)
    }

    fmt.Printf("Updated agentmap %s -> %s\n", version, latest.Version())
    return nil
}
```

### Key Details

- `selfupdate.ChecksumValidator{UniqueFilename: "checksums.txt"}` validates against GoReleaser's checksums.txt automatically
- `DetectLatest` finds the latest GitHub release and matches the right asset for the current OS/arch
- `LessOrEqual` does semver comparison
- `UpdateTo` downloads; extracts from .tar.gz/.zip; replaces the binary atomically; rolls back on failure
- The library handles: OS/arch matching; .tar.gz vs .zip; ARM version detection; macOS universal binaries

### Flags

```go
func init() {
    upgradeCmd.Flags().Bool("check", false, "only check if an update is available")
    rootCmd.AddCommand(upgradeCmd)
}
```

### Permission Handling

On Unix: if the binary is in /usr/local/bin (owned by root); the update will fail with EPERM. Catch this and suggest sudo.
On Windows: less of an issue since the user typically owns the install dir.

### Testing

- Test version comparison logic ("0.1.0" < "0.2.0"; "0.1.0" == "0.1.0"; "dev" rejected)
- Test --check flag output format
- Test graceful error when version is "dev"
- Integration test would require a mock GitHub API (or skip in CI; test manually)
